_Usage.$value: Use base tokens to maintain consistent sizing, spacing, and text styles across all Search Field variants.   Never override these directly in components — inherit through higher-level tokens.

_Documentation.$value: Defines foundational design tokens for the Search Field component.   Includes core measurements, typography, radius, spacing, and icon sizing shared across all types and states.   These tokens serve as building blocks for higher-level component styling.

_Usage.$value: Apply filled type for primary or high-emphasis search areas.   Use this variant when the field needs stronger separation from the background surface.   Do not mix filled and outline types within the same UI region.

_Documentation.$value: Defines color tokens for the filled variant of the Search Field component.   Used for backgrounds, borders, placeholders, and text colors on dark or colored surfaces.   Ensures visual hierarchy through higher contrast and strong fill presence.

_Usage.$value: Use outlined type on light or neutral backgrounds where a subtle field style is preferred.   Ideal for forms, content search, or inline filters.   Avoid using outline type on dark or high-saturation surfaces.

_Usage 2.$value: Use outlined type on light or neutral backgrounds where a subtle field style is preferred.   Ideal for forms, content search, or inline filters.   Avoid using outline type on dark or high-saturation surfaces.

_Documentation.$value: Defines color tokens for the outlined variant of the Search Field component.   Includes neutral background, bordered outlines, and subtle placeholder colors suitable for light surfaces.   Prioritizes simplicity and minimal visual weight.

_Documentation 2.$value: Defines color tokens for the outlined variant of the Search Field component.   Includes neutral background, bordered outlines, and subtle placeholder colors suitable for light surfaces.   Prioritizes simplicity and minimal visual weight.

_Usage.$value: Use error tokens when the user input is invalid or fails validation.   Keep hint text concise and ensure error color contrasts clearly against background and text.

_Documentation.$value: Defines color tokens for error feedback in the Search Field component.   Includes red-tinted border, icon, and hint text for input validation or system error states.

_Usage.$value: Use focus state to emphasize the active input field.   Apply color and border tokens that meet accessibility contrast standards (≥ 4.5:1).   Focus styles should override all other visual states except error.

_Documentation.$value: Defines focused state for the Search Field.   Highlights border and text color while maintaining or slightly elevating background contrast.   Provides visual feedback for active text input.

_Usage.$value: Apply hover tokens to communicate field interactivity when the user’s pointer enters the hit area.   Avoid using hover-only feedback on touch devices.

_Documentation.$value: Defines hover interaction tokens for the Search Field component.   Slightly increases contrast or adjusts border and background to indicate interactivity.

_Usage.$value: Use default state for inactive or unselected fields.   All other states (focus, hover, etc.) should inherit from these values as a base reference.

_Documentation.$value: Defines the default (rest) state for the Search Field component.   Contains neutral tokens for icons, borders, and text before any interaction occurs.

_Usage.$value: Apply success state to confirm correct user input or positive validation.   Use sparingly — only after explicit user interaction or form submission.

_Documentation.$value: Defines tokens for success feedback in the Search Field component.   Uses green-toned borders, icons, and hint text to indicate validated or accepted input.

_Usage.$value: Use disabled tokens when user interaction should be prevented.   Do not rely solely on opacity — ensure clear semantic disabling in code.

_Documentation.$value: Defines tokens for disabled state of the Search Field component.   Reduces opacity and disables interactive colors to indicate non-editable content.

_Usage.$value: Use read-only tokens for pre-filled or uneditable content that must remain visible.   Avoid applying hover or focus feedback to read-only fields.

_Documentation.$value: Defines tokens for the read-only state of the Search Field component.   Visually similar to default state but with reduced focus and hover feedback.
